New York City’s second cat cafe, Koneko, is expected to open next month on Manhattan’s Lower East Side. Patrons can make reservations to eat and drink beer, wine, and sake with cats that are up for adoption for $15 per person per hour, starting September 14.
The animals come from the Anjellicle Cats Rescue, a group that takes in animals from the city’s Animal Care &amp; Control “at risk” list, which means “they are scheduled to be euthanized the following day for behavior or health issues,” according to Koneko’s website.
